div.div:
Add orderId null check and fix OrderPayment query
Added a check in the Invoice Command to terminate the function if orderId is null, thus ensuring orderId is always provided. Also fixed the query in OrderPayment, changing it from incorrectly referencing the product's id to correctly referencing the orderId.

FIX: Remove breadcrumbs function and adjust expiration reference
The breadcrumbs function related to post editing and listing has been removed from the routes in 'platform.php'. The expiration reference was changed in 'DeviceController.php' from customer's expiration to the voucher's expiration, aligning the reference correctly. An unused class was also removed in 'AccountingMain.php'.

Update environment variable names and CORS policy
The commit includes changes in CORS policy for the main application. It now allows specific origins instead of all origins. The form action in "upload.html" and environment variables in the "docker-compose.yml" are also updated. New variables for the "autumn" service are added. Minor changes are also done in the virus scan and download routes.

Refactor code in Invoice.php and adjust product reference
The unnecessary classes named 'Accounting', 'AccountingDocument', and 'ShopCustomer' from the Console Commands Invoice.php file have been removed. Also, in the product retrieval loop, the product reference is now based on the 'product_id' attribute, which replaces the previous direct reference to 'id', ensuring consistency across different parts of the application.

Add new InvoiceList layout and update invoice id reference
The new InvoiceList layout has been added under Orchid\Layouts. The implementation includes the display of actions, order and invoice IDs, and the creation time of invoices. The term 'invoice_id' has been replaced with 'report_id' across invoice-related classes, following a naming convention change. This involved modifications in the order_invoice table migration, Invoice console command, and ReportController.
